France and the rest of Europe in the focus of investors.
On Tuesday, a statistical storm swept through Europe.
The individual countries published their data on their GDP for the third quarter.
The Czech economy stagnated compared to the previous quarter, Germany and France were declining.
Today, the bond market is breaking all records.
Investors are keeping an eye on not only Greece, but also Spain, France, Austria and other countries.
The statistical offices of the European Union, Germany, the Czech Republic and some other European countries published their preliminary forecasts on economic development in the third quarter.
Germany’s GDP is expected to grow by 0.5%, France’s by 0.4%.
Both countries simultaneously corrected their data for the second quarter, in which Germany recorded higher growth than originally expected (growth by 0.3% instead of predicted 0.1%), while France conceded a slight decrease by 0.1% (original data only spoke of stagnation).
The Czech economy grew by 1.5 percent in the third quarter of this year compared to the previous year.
Compared to the previous quarter, however, the gross domestic product stagnated and, according to the Czech Statistical Office, the trend of slowing growth in economic performance was thus confirmed.
The results are therefore worse than analysts’ forecasts.
The most important events:
The Czech economy grew by 1.5 percent in the third quarter of this year compared to the previous year, but stagnated compared to the previous quarter.
According to preliminary and seasonally overestimated data, the German economy grew by 0.5 percent in the third quarter.
Across the euro area and the EU, the economy grew by 0.2 percent between July and September compared to the previous quarter, in line with analysts’ expectations.
The Greek economy shrank by 5.2 percent year-on-year.
The yield on their 10-year government bonds rose by 28.45%.
Yields on Italian and Spanish government bonds rose to their critical limits.
Austria, the Netherlands, France, Belgium and other countries are also starting to feel problems...
