Instead, it is as terrible as "a condemned man who was hanged in secret."
Other observations deal with old Europe falling apart and new kinds of terror.
"The conflict has increasingly become an economic contest," Englund writes, "a war between the factories."
He captures the arrival of what he calls "a new species in the bestiary of the still young century": "the word turned and ideologically convinced mass murderer in a suit who slaughters while sitting behind a desk."
People behave in unpredictable ways and there is frivolous behavior as well as heroism.
Englund discusses the soldiers who were actively trying to infect themselves with a prostitute with a sexually transmitted disease in order to escape the front line service.
