"The health surveys from 1999 and 2006 showed that in just six years the proportion of obese boys increased by 77 percent and that of girls with obesity by 47 percent. Also, obesity had increased dramatically," said the specialist of the IMSS.
He stated that the search for genetic markers was justified because the genetic history of the population of Mexico differed from that of other peoples.
He stated that a Mexican (in) is on average 65 percent Native American, 30 percent European, and 5 percent African, which is reflected in the genes associated with diabetes and obesity.
